# Exporting Request Data

By **clicking** on the `Export` drop-down menu, you can export the data stored in traffic tables.

<img alt="Export drop-down menu options." src="/_images/exports_button.png" center/>

Once a selection is made between `Export all` or `Export current rows`, the data can be exported as either a `.json` or `.csv` file.

<ProContainer>
<b>Export current rows</b> are only available to users with Individual or Team tier subscriptions.
</ProContainer>

::: tip
To further refine which requests are included when exporting the currently displayed rows, use HTTPQL statements.
:::

<img alt="The As JSON and As CSV options." src="/_images/exports_format.png" center/>

The files will be available for download in the `Exports` interface.

<img alt="The Exports interface with two files." src="/_images/exports_files.png" center/>
